          "title": "What Is a Variable?",
          "slug": "what-is-a-variable",
          "order": 1,
          "walkthrough_steps": [
            {
              "image_url": "/images/learn/var-1.svg",
              "caption": "Sometimes in maths, we don't know the exact number. We use a letter to represent it. This letter is called a variable!"
            },
            {
              "image_url": "/images/learn/var-2.svg",
              "caption": "For example: if you have some pencils in a box and you don't know how many, we can call that number 'n'. So n = number of pencils."
            },
            {
              "image_url": "/images/learn/var-3.svg",
              "caption": "A variable can be any letter — x, y, n, or even 'a'. It's just a placeholder for a number we haven't found yet."
            },
            {
              "image_url": "/images/learn/var-4.svg",
              "caption": "If n = 5, that means the box has 5 pencils. If someone adds 2 more, we write: n + 2 = 7. We used the variable to write a rule!"
            }
